'''Katsuraki ni Imasu Honoikaduchi Shrine''' (かつらきにいますほのいかづちじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in Fuefuki, {{ill|lt=Katsuragi|Q659672|qid=Q659672|1=Katsuragi, Nara}}, {{ill|lt=Nara Prefecture|Q131287|qid=Q131287|1=Nara Prefecture}}. It is a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|qid=Q134917286}} ({{ill|lt=Myojin Taisha|Q9610964|qid=Q9610964|1=Myōjin Taisha}}), and under the former {{ill|lt=shrine rank|Q10444029|qid=Q10444029|1=Shakaku}} system it was a {{ill|lt=Gōsha|Q134917316|qid=Q134917316|1=Gō-sha}}. It is commonly called "Fuefuki Shrine."

=== Enshrined deities ===
Its principal deities are {{ill|lt=Honoikazuchi Ōkami|Q10892534|qid=Q10892534|1=Yakusanoikazuchi}} and {{ill|lt=Ame-no-Kagoyama-no-Mikoto|Q10940849|qid=Q10940849|1=Ame-no-Kaguyama}}, with {{ill|lt=Amaterasu|Q455602|qid=Q455602|lt=Ōhirume-no-Muchi-no-Mikoto|1=Amaterasu}}, {{ill|qid=Q125400|lt=Takamimusubi|UNKNOWN|qid=Q125400|lt=Takamimusubi-no-Mikoto|1=Takamimusubi}}, {{ill|lt=Ninigi|Q1056017|qid=Q1056017|lt=Amatsu-hiko Hono-ninigi-no-Mikoto|1=Ninigi-no-Mikoto}}, and Ikohitsuhe-no-Mikoto additionally enshrined. The original deity of Katsuraki ni Imasu Honoikaduchi Shrine was Honoikazuchi Ōkami, while Ame-no-Kagoyama-no-Mikoto was the deity of Fuefuki Shrine. Honoikazuchi Ōkami is also called a thunder deity, but here is worshipped as a fire deity.

=== History ===
=== Overview ===
The date of foundation is unknown; shrine tradition says either in the age of the gods or in the reign of {{ill|lt=Emperor Jinmu|Q200188|qid=Q200188|1=Emperor Jimmu}}. The first documentary appearance is in the ''Buntoku Tennō Jitsuroku'', where in {{ill|lt=Ninju|Q1373077|qid=Q1373077|1=Ninju}} 2 (852), fourth month, it was granted the divine rank of {{ill|lt=Senior Third Rank|Q11123261|qid=Q11123261|1=Senior Third Rank}}. According to the {{ill|lt=Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|Q1052981|qid=Q1052981|1=Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku}}, on the 27th day of the first month of {{ill|lt=Jōgan|Q1075635|qid=Q1075635|lt=Jōgan|1=Jōgan}} 1 ({{ill|lt=859|Q23897|qid=Q23897|1=859}}), it was granted Junior Second Rank. In the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|qid=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}} it is listed as "two seats of Katsuraki ni Imasu Honoikaduchi Shrine in Oshiami District, {{ill|lt=Yamato Province|Q907495|qid=Q907495|1=Yamato Province}}," ranked as myojin taisha and receiving offerings for monthly, aidame, and niiname rites. After this, however, references to the shrine disappear. Shrine tradition says the shrine declined in the Heian period and became a {{ill|lt=subsidiary shrine|Q135009906|qid=Q135009906|1=Massha}} of Fuefuki Shrine in this area.

Fuefuki Shrine is thought to have been founded by the Fuefuki no Muraji clan, who were based here. Its deity Ame-no-Kagoyama-no-Mikoto is their ancestral deity. Behind the honden is an ancient tomb said to be that of {{ill|lt=Taketahori-no-Mikoto|Q97706292|qid=Q97706292|lt=Taketawake-no-Mikoto|1=Taketahori no Mikoto}}, father of Kaiko, ancestor of the Fuefuki no Muraji.

In {{ill|lt=1874|Q7761|qid=Q7761|1=1874}} (Meiji 7), Honoikazuchi-sha, then a sub-shrine of Fuefuki Shrine, was merged into Fuefuki Shrine, the shrine was renamed Katsuraki ni Imasu Honoikaduchi Shrine, and ranked as gōsha.

=== Divine rank ===
* {{ill|lt=Ten'an|Q1075611|qid=Q1075611|lt=Ten'an|1=Ten'an}} 3 ({{ill|lt=859|Q23897|qid=Q23897|1=859}}) {{ill|lt=January 27|Q2284|qid=Q2284|1=January 27}}: from Senior Third Rank, Second Merit Rank to Junior Second Rank, Second Merit Rank ({{ill|lt=Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|Q1052981|qid=Q1052981|1=Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku}}) - written as "Katsuraki Honoikazuchi deity."

=== Precincts ===
There is a Russian-made cannon in the precincts, dedicated by the government after the {{ill|lt=Russo-Japanese War|Q159950|qid=Q159950|1=Russo-Japanese War}}.
