=== Rituals ===
* Otaue Festival
** {{ill|lt=February 11|Q2335|qid=Q2335|1=February 11}}
** Early spring festival announcing spring's arrival in Katsuragi.
** After Kinen-sai is held in the haiden, the Otaue rite is performed in the broad court, including mimed rice-planting actions. Then rice cakes are thrown.
* Nagoshi Festival
** {{ill|lt=July 17|Q2729|qid=Q2729|1=July 17}}
** Parishioners carrying twelve lantern poles visit while singing and accompanying Ise-ondo. The rows of lanterns in the broad court create a fantastic scene.
** Includes dedication performance by the "Katsuragi Taiko Preservation Society."
* Chinka Festival
** {{ill|lt=November 15|Q2982|qid=Q2982|1=November 15}}
** Following old rites, fire is kindled by friction, giving thanks to fire and praying for fire safety.

=== Cultural properties ===
=== Nara Prefecture designated cultural properties ===
* Historic site
** Fuefuki Shrine Kofun - designated March 20, 1998 (Heisei 10).
* Natural monument
** Ichiigashi grove of Fuefuki Shrine - designated March 10, 1997 (listed as Shōwa 62 in source).

